  "commentary": "With SPX at 6567.9 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6550 (-9.79B) and positive gamma wall at 6600 (+6.29B), dealers are likely buying this dip aggressively as we're in breakout regime where they amplify moves. The massive negative GEX concentration from 6540-6560 creates a dangerous zone where any selling will force dealers to sell more, while the 6600 strike acts as the key resistance where dealer selling pressure kicks in. Watch for explosive moves if we break below 6550 or above 6600, as the breakout regime combined with these GEX walls will amplify momentum in either direction.\n\nBottom line: expect big moves with dealers pushing price away from the 6550-6600 zone rather than letting it chop around.",
